        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Since 0.12, Nvim's default statusline is implemented as a special `'statusline'` string. (rather than as an internal C routine)  \nSetting `'statusline'` to empty now defaults to that string. The `set statusline+=` commands you're using are appending to the end of that string instead.\n\nReplace the first two of your `set statusline`s with this:\n```vim\nset statusline=%#ModeNormalColor#%{mode()=='n'?'\\ \\ NORMAL\\ ':''}\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-04-01T07:39:46Z",
